Python, known for its simplicity and versatility, is an excellent programming language for beginners. This project demonstrates how to write your first program, "Hello, World!" in Python, which is a traditional and essential step for anyone starting their coding journey.

In this project, you'll learn:

The basics of Python syntax.
How to display text output using the print() function.
The significance of the "Hello, World!" program in the programming community.
This example serves as a foundation for exploring Python's vast capabilities and marks the start of an exciting adventure into the world of coding. Whether you're learning Python for career development, academic purposes, or personal interest, this project will get you started with confidence.

body: Erlang is a functional programming language for building concurrent, distributed, and fault-tolerant systems. Developed by Ericsson in the 1980s for telecom applications, it features lightweight processes, message passing, and hot code swapping, allowing systems to be updated without downtime. Erlang's robust concurrency model, based on the Actor model, is particularly well-suited for applications requiring high availability and scalability, such as telecommunications, messaging systems, and real-time services. Its strengths in reliability and maintainability have made it popular for modern web applications and distributed systems.
